PREPARING FOR A JOB INTERVIEW:-
# Reviewing the job description :-  Look for the job title, duties and tasks and the skilss required.
# Prepare for questions like why do you have to join this company apart from the other company.
# Understand the competitors, why join this job role, company kind of questions.
# Understand the executive tema like ceo, manager, etc also the culture of the company.

HOW TO FACE A TELEPHONIC INTERVIEW:-
# Start with a polite Hello or Good morning.
# Don't be distracted, answer the phone within 3-4 rings, smile and don't be distracted.
# Seek permission/inform when you put anyone on speaker.
# Ask if you don't understand something and don't interrupt while someone is speaking

CALLING BACK ETIQUETTE:-
# Call back within the time and also specifiy the time clearly rather than just promising.
# Use phrases like could you please explain what you mean?

ENDING A CALL:-
# Allow then to finish and confirm if there will be any future meetings.
# Thanks for their time and end on a positive tone and try not to rush.

VIDEO CONFERENCING:-
# Plan in advance , keep your documents ready.
# Background, stable internet connectivity and noise free background.
# Importance of facial expression, maintain a good posture, dress appropriately, be a good listener.

TELL ME ABOUT YOURSELF:-
# Never repeat your name again and start the introduction if they have already mentioned your name and asked you to introduce.
# Do not start with Myself and always say I'm Ayshath and so on.
# Once your name is mentioned then start with where you're from as "I'm from Ksd" and not "I'm coming from".
# Then you should talk about the Highest qualification.
# Next you should take about your family and not in a descritpive way just, I'm from a family of 6, my parenst and my 3 siblings unless they ask you more about the family.
# Next you should be talking about the achievements.
# Next you should be talking about your hobbies and your interests. Hobbies are the ones  you do in your free time and interests are the one which you find the free time inorder to do them.
# Talk about your personality, what kind of a person are you and so on, best 3 qualities.

STRENGTHS AND WEAKNESSES:-
# Find out a weakness of yours and also get the solution for what have you done inorder to correct the weakness.
# For the strength, always be ready of what is related to the strength that is close to the Job description.
You should be able to explain both the things very well when detailed questions are asked.

